250 g Ground Turkey
½ unit(s) Black Beans
2 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Tomato
56 g Spring Mix
56 g Red Cabbage, shredded
1 unit(s) Lime
2 unit(s) Green Onion
7 g Cilantro
1 unit(s) Diced Pineapple Cup
2 tbsp Spicy Mayo
1 tbsp Jerk Spice Blend
½ tsp Sugar*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.19 tsp Salt*
0.31 tsp Pepper*

Drain and rinse black beans, then pat dry with paper towels.
Thinly slice green onions.
Rough chop cilantro.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice in a small bowl.
Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.
Zest, then juice lime.
Add spicy mayo, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) lime zest, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lime juice and 1 tsp (2 tsp) pineapple juice to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. (NOTE: This is your spicy tropical dressing.)

Add turkey, breadcrumbs, Jerk Spice Blend and half the green onions to a medium bowl. Season with 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) pepper, then combine.
Divide mixture into 8 equal portions (16 portions for 4 ppl).
Roll into balls, then flatten into 1/2-inch-thick patties. (NOTE: Your mixture may be sticky. Lightly wet your hands to make it easier to form patties.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then patties. Cook until golden-brown all over and cooked through, 3-4 min per side.**
Remove from heat.
Transfer patties to a plate.

Whisk together 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lime juice and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil in another medium bowl.
Add tomatoes, pineapple, cilantro, half the black beans (use all for 4 ppl) and remaining green onions, then toss to coat. (NOTE: This is your salsa!)

Add spring mix and cabbage to the bowl with dressing (from step 1). Toss to combine.

Divide salad between plates. Top with patties and salsa.

If you've opted to get turkey, prep and cook turkey the same way the recipe instructs you to prep and cook chicken.